Through his social media page, Brazilian Ricardo Nascimento has confirmed his departure from Mamelodi Sundowns, as reported by SunSport last week. He's making way for Downs' new foreign signing, Bolivian Erwin Saavedr, as they balance their required international quota. "Thanks for the support, Sundowns fans! I really enjoyed and was very happy at mamelodi Sundowns. Thank you," he wrote on Twitter. While being engaged and his contribution appreciated by Sundowns fans, he further wrote: "I really love you guys, thanks, thanks, thank." SunSport reported last week that Nascimento is no longer training with the club, polishing way for incoming 25-year-old Saavedra who hails from Ururo. thanks for the support, Sundowns fans! I really enjoyed and was very happy at Mamelodi sundowns!! Thank You ?????? I really love you guys! Thanks thanks thanks     